[info] Activation of plug-in SEC Inline Transforms successful, version 19.2. - EDGAR/transform

[DQC.US.0154.10071] The filer has reported a value for Foreign Income Tax Rate Differentials that is not using the element defined in the US-GAAP taxonomy. The FASB has elements for Foreign Income Tax Rate Differential percentage amounts and monetary amounts in the taxonomy. These elements are:
1. EffectiveIncomeTaxRateReconciliationForeignIncomeTaxRateDifferential 2. IncomeTaxReconciliationForeignIncomeTaxRateDifferential
The element eltk:IncomeTaxReconciliationRepatriationForeignEarnings with the label "Foreign tax rate differential in subsidiaries" has been used in the filing in the disclosure section "9960749 - Disclosure - TAXES ON INCOME (Reconciliation Of The Theoretical Income Tax Expense To The Actual Income Tax Expense) (Details)" that should be updated to the appropriate US-GAAP element listed above.
Rule Element Id:10071 Rule version: 26.0.9 -
